Kim nh cc gi thuyt thng k (ANOVA assumptions)

Gm cc bc sau:

  • Cc mu c lp (Tha mn bc tin x l)
  • Bin ph thuc l bin lin tc (Tha mn)
  • Cc nhm c phn phi chun hoc gn chun ==> Sai s c phn phi chun

  1. Biu Trn Tri:

    • Th hin mi quan h gia "Category" v gi tr trung bnh iu chnh.
    • "Category 2" c gi tr trung bnh cao nht, trong khi "Category 1" v "Category 3" c gi tr trung bnh thp hn.

  2. Biu Di Tri:

    • Th hin mi quan h gia "Category" v "Paid".
    • "Category 2" c gi tr trung bnh cao nht khi "Paid" = 0, v gim khi "Paid" = 1.
    • Khi Paid = 0, ta thy rng c s tng trng khi Category i t 1 n 3. Ngc li "Paid" = 1 th kt qu lc tng lc gim
    • V tng quan th Paid = 1 s cho kt qu tt hn, c bit l category 2.

Biu Bn Phi

Biu bn phi gm hai phn nh:

  1. Biu Trn Phi:

    • Th hin mi quan h gia "Paid" v gi tr trung bnh iu chnh cho cc nhm "Category".
    • Nhm category2 cho thy hiu qu vt bc khi Paid = 1, trong khi 2 nhm cn li th khng c s thay i khng ng k (tng gim rt t).

  2. Biu Di Phi:

    • Th hin mi quan h gia "Paid" v gi tr trung bnh iu chnh.
    • Gi tr trung bnh tng khi "Paid" chuyn t 0 sang 1.

Kt Lun

  • C "Category" v "Paid" u nh hng ng k n gi tr trung bnh iu chnh ca bin ph thuc.
  • Tng tc gia "Category" v "Paid" cho thy s thay i trong gi tr trung bnh gia cc nhm "Category" ph thuc vo trng thi "Paid".

In[]:
# Kho st ngoi lai theo bin diff
like_data = processed_data["like"]
outliers_index = list()
extreme_outliers_index = list()

for (i in 1:ncol(like_data)) {
  # Tnh ton Q1, Q3 v IQR
  Q1 = quantile(like_data[, i], 0.25, na.rm = TRUE)
  Q3 = quantile(like_data[, i], 0.75, na.rm = TRUE)
  IQR = Q3 - Q1

  # Xc nh ngoi lai
  outliers_index_i = like_data[, i] < (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR) | like_data[, i] > (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR)
  # outliers_i = like_data[like_data[, i] < (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR) | like_data[, i] > (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR), i]

  # Lu tr ngoi lai
  field_name = names(like_data)[i]
  outliers_index[[field_name]] = which(outliers_index_i)

  # Xc nh cc ngoi lai
  extreme_outliers_index_i = like_data[, i] < (Q1 - 3 * IQR) | like_data[, i] > (Q3 + 3 * IQR)
  extreme_outliers_index[[field_name]] = which(extreme_outliers_index_i)
}
# In kt qu theo tng bin ra mn hnh
for (i in 1:ncol(like_data)) {
  print(paste("Bin:", names(like_data)[i]))
  print(paste("S ngoi lai:", length(outliers_index[[names(like_data)[i]]])))
  print(paste("S cc ngoi lai:", length(extreme_outliers_index[[names(like_data)[i]]])))
}

# Tm tng s quan trc ngoi lai v cc ngoi lai thc s
outliers = c()
extreme_outliners = c()
for (i in 1:ncol(like_data)){
    outliers = c(outliers, outliers_index[[names(like_data)[i]]])
    extreme_outliners = c(extreme_outliners, extreme_outliers_index[[names(like_data)[i]]])
}

outliers = unique(outliers)
extreme_outliners = unique(extreme_outliners)
print(paste("Tng s ngoi lai:", length(outliers)))
print(paste("Tng s cc ngoi lai:", length(extreme_outliners)))

  • Category2 (40.21): Khi bin Category chuyn t mc c bn (Category1) sang Category2, bin ph thuc tng trung bnh 40.21 n v.
  • Category3 (46.75): Khi bin Category chuyn t mc c bn (Category1) sang Category3, bin ph thuc tng trung bnh 46.75 n v.
  • Paid1 (31.51): Khi bin Paid chuyn t mc c bn (Paid0) sang Paid1, bin ph thuc tng trung bnh 31.51 n v.
